    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean it feels like a pretty big deal though. if the court can just overturn stuff that people have lived by for 50 years, doesn't that make the whole idea of stable rights kinda meaningless? like, isn't the main point of the court to protect those things rather than just letting states do whatever they want?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
